    <item>
      <title>An Introduction to Sub-Riemannian Geometry</title>
      <link>/talk/subriemannian/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 03 Oct 2022 09:20:48 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>/talk/subriemannian/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title&lt;/strong&gt;: An Introduction to Sub-Riemannian Geometry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker&lt;/strong&gt;: Professor Thomas Bieske&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Date/Time/Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Friday, October 7th, at 12:00pm, NES 102&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract&lt;/strong&gt;: Motivated by real-world activities, we will explore spaces where motion in one or more directions is
restricted. Such spaces, called sub-Riemannian spaces, possess a geometry that behaves quite differently from
traditional Euclidean $\mathbb{R}^n$. Our goal is to understand the interplay between this geometry and properties of solutions to partial differential equations. This talk will be accessible to advanced undergraduate students.  Note: We will also use this talk to deconstruct the concept of a colloquium talk.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
